Speaking in an interview with Le Parisien, PSG midfielder and Italian international <span style="color: red;">Marco Verratti</span> discussed the benefits of no longer being managed by Unai Emery.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;This year, we have a good relationship with the coach and the staff. Each manager has a different way of doing things with his players, of making them understand things. <span style="color: red;">Sometimes with Emery, things were quite difficult&hellip; </span>Is the difference relating to human personality? Yes I think so. Tuchel isn&rsquo;t playing around&hellip; But coming to a training session with a shut-off face, that doesn&rsquo;t work. We have found our smile again, we had lost it a little.&rdquo;

